Bryan Joseph Conquest (20 July 1930 â€“ 2 January 2018) was an Australian politician. Born in Quilpie, Queensland, he was a managing director and Bundaberg City Councillor before entering politics. In 1984, he was elected to the Australian House of Representatives as the National member for the new notionally Labor seat of Hinkler. Conquest was defeated in 1987.
